cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use metajudge in your work, please cite it as below."
title: "metajudge: a reliability and DIF report card for LLM-judge and human-rater scoring instruments"
abstract: >-
  metajudge audits a multi-rater ordinal scoring instrument, an LLM-as-judge or
  a human rater panel, for reliability (Krippendorff's alpha and ICC) and
  differential item functioning across output strata, and prints a one-screen
  report card. Every statistic is pinned to an external reference implementation.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Brittany Reese
    family-names: Markides
version: 0.1.0
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/brittanyreese/metajudge"
url: "https://github.com/brittanyreese/metajudge"
keywords:
  - llm-judge
  - psychometrics
  - reliability
  - differential-item-functioning
  - evaluation
